l id="e23" value="count the ~10^19 soil invertebrates" style="edgeStyle=none;curved=1;html=1;endArrow=block;endFill=1;strokeColor=#9aa6b3;fontSize=9;fontColor=#5b6675;strokeColor=#8a5fb0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="w1_2_3_4_5_9_11_12" target="w1_2_3_4_5_9_11_12_13"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"><Array as="points"><mxPoint x="835" y="1301"/><mxPoint x="842" y="1303"/><mxPoint x="842" y="1303"/><mxPoint x="842" y="1303"/><mxPoint x="1206" y="1396"/></Array></mxGeometry></mxCell><object label="Animals matter a lot&lt;br&gt;(RP welfare ranges)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+5]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;(Bob Fischer, Brian Tomasik)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Replace the neuron-count proxy with Rethink Priorities&#x27; welfare-range estimates (Fischer et al.) and count invertebrates — shrimp, insects, and the ~10^19 soil animals. Under RP medians a chicken&#x27;s welfare range is a third of a human&#x27;s, not a fiftieth, and wild/soil invertebrates carry significant aggregate (nematode) weight, so invertebrate work dominates. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 5 animals_matter_a_lot" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx1Vm1z4jYQ%2Fis7TDuFDCHGkF6PDh9IwiWZcr1MjvamEzKOsNdYPVnySHIcN5f%2F3pXNa4BPGO%2Fq2d1nn135tRFhzHJhL1WEjUHj7AyGwyFMNeMSrIJQs%2F9KeigkzHLf6%2FahUFpEzxwLKLqBH%2FSCfnAOTWNVBuctd3gmCWRkTJ5mlisJYUJYA%2FAgY1qFCWfCQXU%2F%2BtCFmOmAFawMkjxl0qwMPjDJUyZMYFSKRcLsytKDOLe5xuWBIGXWog4KbpMg4iZUubRcLlbufZBq%2B32wc3rldb4Ot4RjgVC2qmPMwgTYphhugMFdaRN6jrlAIJo2ZnMG1iXLosi0QSNxyyUaULoC03hKHLAUKQY39N4mWNPzi6G6ZFhh%2FA6hSjNlXBlrBzorIyREesVNhWYskxETSiKk1DzRgad1b8bPTy5VdxxfMgwtHXxmIkdQcYWwaWOnArtAY2Gel5C7MO6gwe3CBjC6BcNitCU07zEqlIrgnpyYDpNWjXE9%2FnN8P5qOr2BewgIlamaxk5Ur5WDE7Q5ZJ2RsU4dsnZLjk5AqrCuuKWvAOHY%2FRDa6Rii9IKYyTc3SJcwpRMxDTs9tuBh%2F%2BnI%2FJiY0ExVCgXyRuJ4TL0I5LSf8qe6fUAupNDUcPno%2Fw%2BUtNJWmqk9VfJqyheQ2jxAuvkzHl64yo%2FLsD27DBOUVE%2BUd6r9MBEN4nUmADFUm8AZFhtHa4nW8cxfQ65w7nwKFmCNlck2NdBC1i9etfbyuc6oUijpmoc2ZuGDy%2B99Vv5xr70ikkwPQJ9DswukxuNZMvs3kItopxOXi9ZfJeP5MsjTec%2BgtK%2FJ8SpfxdM9hVY1PNdtE7Ni7Hd9Z%2Bx%2BIzSLbNfme52wf%2BpTETBZcRPN8YXZ9fq19fvMrHyZEjPsl%2BGvKda3Pdx6V3SF4S42NH4qr0eQfYM%2Bo3YBkJPyfHgfbUot2ZGh5uhzajcxCRUYSIUr7brDoOHu3BSHLrXFq5tYJK1RuoIfw4Pr7CsQ7DmDWmKiQpOlkB99r3c0abSiidTkDSJHJ5kFhtkgBXXhr70Je82esR0qUh8G2NXEc4xvpDdyqp3I0d7tg9PlT6zDijooOQ45uP8MZXC6xxtJqzGjRYa5NwrMjsNvaOww7pQ7duA2PMEG2yPEw0o5KHRJNWs%2FfQ%2Fua0L7JgEqn2wrhTqt%2FiccjLdlWdw3p9fYT%2FEYqp5vDEI6BZlKnmtEKJiFFaI4Quj8bywgHiJ1MPo2vjhD4bnyOteb4uj%2BMuzd1G%2BBHN3GalpC704Yw4cZ2NNLYGWxWf4zS9qJs1hPRhtcfLz%2FgpbMV461Fq2vuLqkhLIEevMflIE8PXnPTm9uvm2kcQPUZwYnw%2BequoznnlIWhWdy6OSmC89iOPpONt%2F8Bh94bWg%3D%3D" id="w1_2_3_4_5"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f5d3b8;strokeColor=#cc7a33;fontColor=#5a300e;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1615" y="0" width="244" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Suffering-focused&lt;br&gt;ethics&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+5+6]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;▼ 23 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot + suffering_focused&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Asymmetry: averting intense suffering takes priority over creating happiness. Factory farming, malaria and the worst wild-animal conditions weigh up; speculative future-flourishing bets weigh down. Arises most naturally from taking animal suffering seriously, so it requires animals_somewhat. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 6 suffering_focused" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_3_4_5_6.drawio" id="w1_2_3_4_5_6"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f2ccc0;strokeColor=#c96a4a;fontColor=#5a2410;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1438" y="239" width="244" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Living in&lt;br&gt;a simulation&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+5+9]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;(Nick Bostrom)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot + living_in_simulation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If most observers like us are simulated, the astronomical future that justified x-risk work probably gets switched off long before it happens. The same expected-value reasoning that bought astronomical stakes now attenuates them: future-facing value is multiplied by the probability the simulation keeps running, and the ranking slides back toward the present. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 9 living_in_simulation" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx1Vm1z4jYQ%2Fis7TDuFDCHGkF5Dhw8kIS9TrpfJ0d50QsYR9hqrJ0seScahufz3rmxeA3zCeFfP7j777MpvtQhjlgt7pSKs9WpnZ9Dv92GsGZdgFYSa%2Fbegh0LCJPe9dhcKpUU051hA0Q78oBN0g%2FPgAurGqgwuGu74RBLMwJg8zSxXEsKE0HrgQca0ChPOhANrX%2FjQhpjpgBVsESR5yqRZGXxgkqdMmMCoFIuE2ZWlA3Fuc43LA0HKrEUdFNwmQcRNqHJpuZyt3Lsg1fb7YOf0yut8HW4JxwKh1iEvQPC5O8tlYHiaC%2BbKKqscsjABtimVG2DwsLAJPcdcIBCNG7M5A%2BtKYVFkmqCRuOcSDShdgmk8JYZYipQBN%2FTeJliR94uhqmVYYvwOoUozZVyRawc6KyMkRHrFTYlmLJMRE0oipNRc0YKXde%2BG8xeXqjuOrxmGlg7OmcgRVFwibNrcKsEu0ViY5gvIXRh30OB2YT0Y3INhMdoF1B8xKpSK4JGcmA6TRoVxO%2Fxz%2BDgYD69huoAZStTMYitbrJSFEbc7ZJ