i33Ni2RhpXg43qj1Hans0a9SS14PXHyw94aa9FeWvSlTdxy20Ic6BH72l%2BATzsXI8P1zdfVlM8gOqbhRPpk8WOpPuBUxaGZnht41IE57EefSz33v4D7%2FI49w%3D%3D" id="w1_2_3_4_5_9_13"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#c9b3dd;strokeColor=#4a2a78;fontColor=#201040;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="-0" y="1434" width="244" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Two-envelope welfare&lt;br&gt;skepticism&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+5+10]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;(Nuno Sempere)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot + two_envelope_welfare_skepticism&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Rethink Priorities&#x27; mainline welfare ranges are expectations over deep sentience uncertainty, and cross-species welfare comparisons hit the two-envelope problem. Nuno Sempere&#x27;s Bayesian adjustment shrinks the smallest animals&#x27; welfare ranges by one to two orders of magnitude. Chickens are barely affected; shrimp and insects fall far enough that corporate chicken campaigns retake the top of the animal slate. Only bites once the RP welfare ranges are in play, so it requires animals_matter_a_lot. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 10 two_envelope_welfare_skepticism" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx1lm1z4jYQx7%2FKDtNOIUOIcaDXo8MLkpCHKdfL5GgznZBxhL3G6smSR5JxaC7fvSubxwCvQtjVb5%2F%2BK%2FFWizBmubCXKsJar3Z2Bv1%2BH8aacQlWQajZfwv6UEiY5L7X7kChtIjmHAso2oEfnAedoBu0PagbqzJoew0HmEgCDYzJ08xyJSFMiNcDDzKmVZhwJhyu%2FdmHNsRMB6xgiyDJUybNyuADkzxlwgRGpVgkzK4s5xDnNte4PBCkzFrUQcFtEkTchCqXlsvZyr0DUm1%2FH%2BycXnl11%2BGWOBYItQ5J9dlCBSjnKFSGQYGC0sbAfEcqMOQmLSsesjABtimbG2Bwv7AJfY65QKCmbszmDKwri0WRaYJGmgSXaEDpEqbxlLrFUqRsuKHvbYJVI38x1AEZlozfIVRppowreO1AZ2WERKSvuClpxjIZMaEkQkqjFi14WU9yOH9xqbrj%2BJp